<subSubSection id="269F6561DC31CD11FF0C842C54D8FBC3" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC31CD10FF0C842C514AF92D" blockId="72.[189,303,1638,1664]" box="[189,303,1638,1664]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<heading id="35728186DC31CD10FF0C842C514AF92D" bold="true" box="[189,303,1638,1664]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" reason="3">
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FF0C842C514AF92D" bold="true" box="[189,303,1638,1664]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC31CD10FF0C84DF51C9F829" blockId="72.[189,1399,1685,1924]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
The combination of characters illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC31CD10FD6F84DF53EEF902" author="Uchida S." box="[734,907,1685,1711]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="535 - 556" refId="ref37320" refString="Uchida S. 1949. Studies on the biting-lice (Mallophaga) of Japan and adjacent territories (Suborder Ischnocera Pt II). The Japanese Medical Journal 1: 535 - 556. https: // doi. org / 10.7883 / yoken 1948.1.535" type="journal article" year="1949">Uchida (1949)</bibRefCitation>
are incompatible with all known genera in the 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FEA084F351FFF97E" box="[273,410,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Philopterus</emphasis>
-complex sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC31CD10FDD584F3529DF97E" author="Mey E." box="[612,760,1721,1747]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="149 - 203" refId="ref36265" refString="Mey E. 2004. Zur Taxonomie, Verbreitung und parasitophyletischer Evidenz des Philopterus - Komplexes (Insecta, Phthiraptera, Ischnocera). Ornithologischer Anzeiger 43: 149 - 203." type="journal article" year="2004">Mey (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC31CD10FCB984F35404F97E" author="Hopkins G. H. E. &amp; Clay T." box="[776,1121,1721,1748]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="ref35833" refString="Hopkins G. H. E. &amp; Clay T. 1952. A Check List of the Genera and Species of Mallophaga. British Museum (Natural History), London, United Kingdom. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 118844" type="book" year="1952">Hopkins &amp; Clay (1952: 91)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FF0C849651C3F95B" box="[189,422,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Craspedorrhynchus</emphasis>
“with some doubt”, but did not expand on this placement. Indeed, the characters in the original illustration and description of this species agree well with those of most species of 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FF0C856E51C3F893" box="[189,422,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Craspedorrhynchus</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC31CD10FE0B856E52C9F893" author="Uchida S." box="[442,684,1827,1854]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="535 - 556" refId="ref37320" refString="Uchida S. 1949. Studies on the biting-lice (Mallophaga) of Japan and adjacent territories (Suborder Ischnocera Pt II). The Japanese Medical Journal 1: 535 - 556. https: // doi. org / 10.7883 / yoken 1948.1.535" type="journal article" year="1949">Uchida (1949: 546)</bibRefCitation>
also stated that this species belonged to 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FB06856E54A2F893" box="[1207,1223,1828,1854]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">“</emphasis>
Piaget’s group 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FF0C850D51E4F8CC" box="[189,385,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Delatatoclypeati</emphasis>
infesting the birds of prey”, further supporting the removal of this species to 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FF0C852051C3F829" box="[189,422,1898,1924]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Craspedorrhynchus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC31CD11FF0C85E15402FDB1" blockId="72.[189,1399,1963,2025]" lastBlockId="73.[187,1401,265,540]" lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Specifically, the hyaline margin of 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC31CD10FDD485E1533FF868" box="[613,858,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Philopterus hiyodori</emphasis>
is without median sclerotization, emarginate medially, and extends lateral to the marginal carina. The dorsal anterior plate is elongate and tongue-like, without lateral extensions near 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FD8583435239FE8E" box="[564,604,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">ads</emphasis>
. At least some preantennal setae appear to be dorsal, and the two anterior-most of these appear to be elongated and thickened compared to the other illustrated preantennal setae. The eyes are extended posteriorly.Apart from the 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FC87831B5335FEC7" box="[822,848,337,362]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">os</emphasis>
, three temporal setae on each side are illustrated as macrosetae; the identity of these is not clear, but they appear to be 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FC59833E545EFE23" box="[1000,1083,372,398]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">mts1–3</emphasis>
. In the illustration, there is a dotted line along the median pterothorax, which is described as “separated by a narrow, uncoloured, mesal linear space” in the text; this suggests that the pterothorax is divided by a median suture. All these characters are found in 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FE7E839452D0FE55" box="[463,693,478,504]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Craspedorrhynchus</emphasis>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FD42839453B2FE55" author="Gallego J. &amp; Martin Mateo M. P. &amp; Aguirre J. M." box="[755,983,478,505]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="31 - 66" refId="ref35388" refString="Gallego J., Martin Mateo M. P. &amp; Aguirre J. M. 1987. Malofagos de rapaces espanolas. II. Las especies de genero Craspedorrhynchus Keler, 1938 parasitas de Falconiformes, con descripcion de tres especies nuevas. Eos 63: 31 - 66." type="journal article" year="1987">
Gállego 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FCE6839553EFFE55" box="[855,906,478,504]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">et al</emphasis>
. 1987
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FC528395543BFE55" author="Mey E." box="[995,1118,478,505]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="117 - 132" refId="ref36229" refString="Mey E. 2001. A new Craspedorrhynchus species (Phthiraptera, Ischnocera) from Australia, with an annotated checklist of this chewing louse genus. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 48: 117 - 132." type="journal article" year="2001">Mey 2001</bibRefCitation>
), except that posteriorly extended eyes are limited to a few species in this genus (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FC3780485467FDB1" author="Mey E." box="[902,1026,514,540]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="117 - 132" refId="ref36229" refString="Mey E. 2001. A new Craspedorrhynchus species (Phthiraptera, Ischnocera) from Australia, with an annotated checklist of this chewing louse genus. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 48: 117 - 132." type="journal article" year="2001">Mey 2001</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 14).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC30CD11FF0C800E5345FC9E" blockId="73.[188,1399,579,819]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FF0C800E512DFDF3" author="Mey E." box="[189,328,580,606]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="117 - 132" refId="ref36229" refString="Mey E. 2001. A new Craspedorrhynchus species (Phthiraptera, Ischnocera) from Australia, with an annotated checklist of this chewing louse genus. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 48: 117 - 132." type="journal article" year="2001">Mey (2001)</bibRefCitation>
treated this species as a member of 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FD42800953F4FDF0" box="[755,913,579,605]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Tritrabeculus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FC298009545CFDF3" author="Uchida S." box="[920,1081,579,606]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="303 - 326" refId="ref37275" refString="Uchida S. 1948. Studies on the biting-lice (Mallophaga) of Japan and adjacent territories (Suborder Ischnocera Pt I). The Japanese Medical Journal 1: 303 - 326. https: // doi. org / 10.7883 / yoken 1948.1.303" type="journal article" year="1948">Uchida, 1948</bibRefCitation>
, but gave no details. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FF0C8022512EFD2C" author="Mey E." box="[189,331,615,642]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="149 - 203" refId="ref36265" refString="Mey E. 2004. Zur Taxonomie, Verbreitung und parasitophyletischer Evidenz des Philopterus - Komplexes (Insecta, Phthiraptera, Ischnocera). Ornithologischer Anzeiger 43: 149 - 203." type="journal article" year="2004">Mey (2004)</bibRefCitation>
did not include 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FDA4802D52CEFD2C" box="[533,683,615,641]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Ph. hiyodori</emphasis>
in 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FD67802D5311FD2C" box="[726,884,615,641]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Tritrabeculus</emphasis>
, limiting this genus to two species known from cuckoo-shrikes. The following characters mentioned or illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FBEA80C0556FFD08" author="Uchida S." box="[1115,1290,650,677]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="535 - 556" refId="ref37320" refString="Uchida S. 1949. Studies on the biting-lice (Mallophaga) of Japan and adjacent territories (Suborder Ischnocera Pt II). The Japanese Medical Journal 1: 535 - 556. https: // doi. org / 10.7883 / yoken 1948.1.535" type="journal article" year="1949">Uchida (1949)</bibRefCitation>
separate 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FF0C80E45135FD65" box="[189,336,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Ph. hiyodori</emphasis>
from 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FE2B80E45252FD65" box="[410,567,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Tritrabeculus</emphasis>
: frons hyaline throughout in 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FC2280E45442FD65" box="[915,1063,686,712]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Ph. hiyodori</emphasis>
, but medianly sclerotized in 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FF0F8098513EFD41" box="[190,347,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Tritrabeculus</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FEDD80985264FD41" box="[364,513,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Ph. hiyodori</emphasis>
with four temporal macrosetae, but 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FC0880985432FD41" box="[953,1111,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Tritrabeculus</emphasis>
with only two temporal macrosetae; at least two preantennal setae on each side situated on the hyaline frons in 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FB0180BF5527FCA2" box="[1200,1346,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Ph. hiyodori</emphasis>
, but no setae situated in hyaline section in 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FDCA8153537CFC9E" box="[635,793,793,819]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Tritrabeculus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E3A36EADC30CD11FF0C811154D8FBC3" blockId="73.[188,1399,858,1134]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
We hereby move 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FE398110521EFCD9" box="[392,635,858,884]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Philopterus hiyodori</emphasis>
to the genus 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FCA78110539AFCD9" box="[790,1023,858,884]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Craspedorrhynchus</emphasis>
, where it was previously placed by 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FF5581345260FC34" author="Hopkins G. H. E. &amp; Clay T." box="[228,517,894,921]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refId="ref35833" refString="Hopkins G. H. E. &amp; Clay T. 1952. A Check List of the Genera and Species of Mallophaga. British Museum (Natural History), London, United Kingdom. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 118844" type="book" year="1952">Hopkins &amp; Clay (1952)</bibRefCitation>
. As this genus is otherwise only found on raptors, it seems probable that 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FF0C81E8512BFC16" box="[189,334,929,956]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Cr. hiyodori</emphasis>
was described from stragglers. In the same publication, 
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FBB981EB54D3FC11" author="Uchida S." box="[1032,1206,929,956]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="535 - 556" refId="ref37320" refString="Uchida S. 1949. Studies on the biting-lice (Mallophaga) of Japan and adjacent territories (Suborder Ischnocera Pt II). The Japanese Medical Journal 1: 535 - 556. https: // doi. org / 10.7883 / yoken 1948.1.535" type="journal article" year="1949">Uchida (1949)</bibRefCitation>
lists records of 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FF0C818F51EBFC72" box="[189,398,965,991]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Philopterus milvi</emphasis>
(Mjöberg, 1910) [= 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FD24818F5477FC72" box="[661,1042,965,991]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Craspedorrhynchus spathulatus</emphasis>
(Giebel, 1875)], 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FB5F818F5082FBAF" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Philopterus nisi</emphasis>
(Denny, 1842), and 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FE6B81A35374FBAE" box="[474,785,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Philopterus platyrhynchus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0A144B1BDC30CD11FC9181A353A3FBAE" author="Nitzsch C. L." box="[800,966,1001,1027]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="261 - 318" refId="ref36710" refString="Nitzsch C. L. 1818. Die Familien und Gattungen der Thierinsekten (Insecta epizoica); als ein Prodromus einer Naturgeschichte derselben. E. F. Germar's Magazin der Entomologie 3: 261 - 318." type="journal article" year="1818">Nitzsch, 1818</bibRefCitation>
) [= 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FC4881A35512FBAE" box="[1017,1399,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Craspedorrhynchus haematopus</emphasis>
(Scopoli, 1763)], but none of his material is from the same locality as his specimens of 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FB508647550AFB8B" box="[1249,1391,1036,1063]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Cr. hiyodori</emphasis>
. A detailed study of the 
<typeStatus id="B13E8848DC30CD11FE7F867A5264FBE7" box="[462,513,1072,1098]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">type</typeStatus>
specimens, if they remain, will be needed to establish whether 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FB58867A5513FBE7" box="[1257,1398,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Cr. hiyodori</emphasis>
is synonymous with any of the other species of 
<emphasis id="5CF1EAF8DC30CD11FD5A861953B1FBC0" box="[747,980,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Craspedorrhynchus</emphasis>
known from 
<collectingCountry id="1692767ADC30CD11FBC3861E54DCFBC3" box="[1138,1209,1108,1134]" name="Japan" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
